A two-year-old girl has died and up to four children have been rescued in a house fire.

Two fire crews were called to the blaze in Conisbrough, near Doncaster, South Yorkshire, just before 8pm yesterday after a neighbour raised the alarm.

The toddler was rescued from a bedroom window and taken to hospital, but later died from her injuries.

